results.name: Sum of the reversals of the divisors of n.
link: Indranil Ghosh, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..50000
example: The divisors of 10 are 1,2,5,10, which reversed are 1,2,5,1, summing to 9. Therefore a(10) = 9.
mathematica: f[n_] := FromDigits[Reverse[IntegerDigits[n]]]; g[n_] := Apply[Plus, Map[f, Divisors[n]]]; Table[g[i], {i, 1, 40}]
